text: Else Marie Fjære-Fredriksen (born 2 July 1944) is a former Norwegian long track speed skater, who was active in the 1950s and 1960s. Fjære represented her nation at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1960, finishing 26th overall. She competed at the 1963 and 1964 Norwegian Allround Championships, finishing fourth at both occasions. == Records== === Personal records === ==References== ==External links== * Category:1944 births Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Date of birth missing (living people) Category:Norwegian female speed skaters Category:Living people
